%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant Pods as Training Pods<br/>(master/worker)
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>(pod-to-pod DNS)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)
    participant CertCtrl as cert-controller<br/>(in-process)

    Note over User,Pods: Flow 1: Training Job Submission and Reconciliation

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create PyTorchJob<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS (TLS self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Result (Allow/Deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job Created / Rejected

    Note over Controller,Pods: Reconciliation Loop

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (PyTorchJob created)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create headless Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Service created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create master Pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Pod created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create worker Pods (0..N)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Pods created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>(PyTorch only)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: NetworkPolicy created

    Note over Pods,HeadlessSvc: Distributed Training Communication

    Pods->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup for peers<br/>worker-0.svc, worker-1.svc...
    HeadlessSvc-->>Pods: Pod IP addresses
    Pods->>Pods: Framework-specific communication<br/>TCP plaintext (NetworkPolicy restricted)

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Status Updates

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update job status<br/>(Running/Succeeded/Failed)
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job status available

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>(job counts, pod groups, services)

    Note over CertCtrl,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Webhook Certificate Management

    CertCtrl->>K8sAPI: Read/Update Secret<br/>(webhook-cert) 443/TCP HTTPS
    CertCtrl->>K8sAPI: Update ValidatingWebhookConfiguration<br/>caBundle 443/TCP HTTPS
    K8sAPI-->>CertCtrl: Acknowledged
